Click on the slide show to see this week’s featured properties in New York City:
• In Bedford Stuyvesant, Brooklyn, a townhouse with a three-bedroom, three-and-a-half bath triplex with en suite baths, a deck and a terrace, and a two-bedroom, one-bath garden apartment.
• On the Upper East Side, a one-bedroom, one-bath apartment with high ceilings, a wood-burning fireplace and central air conditioning in a prewar doorman building.
• In the Flatiron District, a studio with discrete sleeping quarters in a prewar building converted in 2008 by the designer Jade Jagger.
